commit.message:
Fixed route on view method for unit test

Using 'route4' as route argument lead to the wrong function being
called. Fixed this by calling the route differently.

Add unit testfor checking @method with @route decorators

If a route is set explicitly on a method with the @route decorator, the
@method decorator has no effect. This is by design, because you can
specify the method within the @route decorator.

Add two unit tests for the @method decorator

These unit tests check that the @method decorator works at all and check
that a method can be decorated multiple times.

Add @method decorator and handling

Using the @method decorator, you can specify for which http method your
class method will be called. This is useful if you cannot use the
default_methods on you class because not all class methods implement the
entire list and if you do not want to use the @route decorator, which
supports method definition as well, because you do not want to lose the
flexibility of classful creating the url rules for you.
